Value.value: *Looks at your coins* Whose head is that meant to be? Duke Montgomery? Never heard of him. Nope, no way I'm accepting that.
*Looks at your coins* Whose head is that meant to be? Duke Montgomery? Never heard of him. Nope, no way I'm accepting that, stunty.
Go bury yerself, ya sooty sod. I'd rather flush me wares down the sewers than serve ya.
Hoohoo! La de blummin' da! Sorry, pointy ears, but we don't sell any lettuce leaves here. Or serve 'em.
*he takes a disdainful look at you, and spits a large brown glob of what looks like chewing tobacco on the ground near your feet, splattering your boots.*
What in all the hells names are you, ya gilly git? Get outa my shop before I fry ya!
*pulls a crash helmet out and puts it securely on his head* No, no and no. Whatever yer selling, I don't want it, and whatever yer buying, I aint got it.
Would ya look at that? It looks like one o' those inventors, but even uglier. Well, I'm not serving them, and I'm not serving you, neither.

Hmmm. You're one o' them pointy eared sods, aren't ya? Well, your kind can take our women, but ya can't shop at our stores. *looks confused a moment* Wait? Did  I just say ya could take our women? That can't be right.
Get out me shop, ya thieving git. I've met your kind before!
*he takes a disdainful look at you, and spits a large brown glob of what looks like chewing tobacco on the ground near your feet, splattering your boots.*
Buzz off, barbie. I'm not serving ya, and I don't want ya landing on me pies.
Get out me shop, ya snotty little git, before I throw ya out in little pieces.
Sod off, rover. Your money's no good here, ya dog faced cur!
I don't care if you're Torm Himself, yer not local, an' I'm not bleedin' servin' ya.
Shift it, ya shifty little swine. Yer not laying one horny hoof on my goods!
I'm not serving your lot. Get back to yer own plane, and stop nicking our jobs!
Let me put this simply for ya, ya thick git. SOD…OFF…OUTTA…MY…SHOP!
Well, you didn't do bad. But that still don't look like proper money to me.
Well, you didn't do bad. But that still don't look like proper money to me, fatty.
Hero or no, I'm still not serving ya, ya grey git.
Hero or no, I'm still not serving ya, ya pointy eared sod.
*in a low growl* Get the hells outta my shop, ya monster.
Hero or no, I don't serve seafood.
Yeah, yeah, yeah, so you saved the day. Doesn't mean yer getting anything from me!
You want gratitude? Well I'm not selling ya any.
Look Legoland, I'm not serving ya. Yer not from round here, are ya?
I don't care if yer a hero. That don't look like proper money to me, shorty.
*in a low growl* Get the hells outta my shop, ya monster.
I don't believe a little thing like you could have saved the day. I'm not servin' ya. I just told ya I didn't believe it, didn't I?
So ya helped sum peeps. What did ya do? Sneeze on 'em foes and drown 'em? Nope, I'm still not servin' ya.
So ya saved the day. What did ya do? Bite their ankle til they fell over? Nope, I'm still not servin' ya.
Praise be, it's a miracle, ya saved the day! *he says sarcastically* But yer still not getting any o' my stuff. Locals only.
Hmmm. I still don't trust yer. And this is a local shop, for local people.
Hmmm. I still don't trust yer. And this is a local shop, for local people.
So you saved the day. You bashed 'em good, eh? I still don't want you in here stinking my shop out though.
